         <abstract>
            <p>A generalized Chebyshev interpolation procedure increasing a fixed number of sample points at a time is developed and analyzed. It is incorporated into an efficient automatic quadrature scheme of Clenshaw-Curtis type. Numerical examples indicate that the present method is efficient not only for well-behaved functions but for those with discontinuous low order derivatives by virtue of adequate error estimation as well as saving of sample points.</p>
          </abstract>
